Beast Mom by @kim_imas_author is a speculative fiction novel coming out on 8/29 and was such a good read! 📖 The novel follows Harriet or Harry as she’s affectionately known to her family and friends. She’s a busy woman being stretched in many different directions. Harry is a full time working mother of 3 and wife to her college sweetheart. She has to work, take care of her kids, go to PTA meetings (that seem to largely be run by a man who belittles the concerns of the women/moms in the meetings), go food shopping (multiple times to adhere to the precise healthy needs required by the daycare/pre-school her twins go to), and also find time to connect with her husband. 

Soon, Harry starts to get this weird feeling when she feels like she’s getting upset and on the verge of losing it. She starts turning into a large monster with claws, horns, etc. The monster allows her to let off some of her steam and maybe teach those who are wronging her a lesson or two before she goes back to her normal, human body. 👿 

What does it all mean and can she control the monster? Soon, she learns other moms in her community are also going through some changes.

The book was so good and will probably be (at times frustratingly) relatable for so many readers! The book leaves some things open at the end for a follow up, which the author tells me is the plan and I can’t wait to see what happens next for Harry and the other women! 

My full review is on the blog ✨

Daughter of the Siren Queen by @tricialevenseller is the follow up to Daughter of the Pirate King and definitely lived up to book 1! 📚 This novel picks up a little after the end of Daughter of the Pirate King with Alosa and her crew tracking down the last piece of the map to Isla de Canta and its supposed treasure. Her crew now includes Riden, the pirate who held her “captive” in book 1, and who she may or may not be in love with 😍. 

Pretty early in the book Alosa learns that not only was her father very tough on her growing up as he trained her to be a fierce pirate and weapon, but he’s been lying to her her whole life. Now she must race him to the treasure before he can become even more powerful and before he can kill her and her crew. 🏴‍☠️🧜‍♀️

This was a great sequel and I love Alosa and Riden and their slow burn! ❤️ I could not put the book down and got through it so fast 📖.

The Cheat Sheet by @authorsarahadams has been on my tbr for a long time because I heard it’s a super cute romcom and it definitely was! 💚

The novel follows Bree Camden and Nathan Donelson - best friends since high school. Now Bree is a ballet teacher and studio owner and Nathan is a star quarterback in the NFL. They know everything about each other, except for the fact that they’ve both been in love with each other for since high school 👀. After a reporter witnesses a sweet moment between them one night rumors start flying that they are a couple and the public absolutely loves it. For various reasons they decide to fake date until playoffs are over. Can these few weeks of fake dating help them admit their true feelings to each other? 📖💚

I loved this book and it was such a quick read! I loved Bree and Nathan and how close they were. I can’t wait for the spin-off sequel next year! 🏈🩰

Read this if you want a friends to lovers, fake dating, slow burn, sports romance romcom 📚. My full review is on the blog ✨

Beneath Black Sails by @claresager is my latest read for my summer of pirates! 🏴‍☠️ It is the first book in a completed 4 book series and was a really fun read! It follows Lady Vice, a notorious pirate  and young woman who wants to captain her own ship more than anything. Knigh Blackwood is a pirate hunter for the Royal Navy. There is a large bounty on Vice that Knigh is hoping to collect to pay off his family’s debts and return his upper class family to their good name. 

Vice and Knigh should be enemies but when a deal is struck between her captain and the Royal Navy making them privateers for the Queen they must work closely together. Maybe searching for a rumored long lost treasure will answer all their prayers 🏴‍☠️⚓️📖💕

This was such a fun read and I love Vice and Knigh. There were also a few plot twists too that I loved! 📖

Read this if you want a spicy pirate fantasy romance with the enemies to lovers and forced proximity tropes. There is also sort of another trope, but I can’t say without spoiling! 🤐📚

I’m looking forward to starting book 2 soon! My full review is on the blog ✨

A Game of Gods by Scarlett St. Clair is the latest book in the A Touch of Darkness series and the last book in the Hades Saga 🖤. It takes place during the same time as A Touch of Malice, but instead of Persephone’s POV it is from Hades, Dionysus, and Theseus’s POVs. I loved the book and loved being back in that world with characters I love 📖🖤. Honestly, I forgot a lot of what happened in Malice until I read this and then it jogged my memory 😂. I have a theory about what the last book is going to be about! 

Overall, loved the book and being back with Hades & Persephone 🖤. Of course Hecate and Hermes were so good too. I also loved Dionysus and Ariadne in the book! I hope Scarlett St. Clair does books for them and for Aphrodite & Hephaestus 🔥. Maybe Apollo too!

Read this series if you want a spicy Greek mythology retelling 📚🖤. My full review is on the blog ✨

🌴 The Honeymoon Crashers 🌴 by @christinalauren 

I loved The Unhoneymooners so I was excited for this book following Olive’s sister, Ami, as she tries to plan the perfect wedding for Olive and Ethan. This was an audiobook exclusive and I’m not an audiobook person, but had to listen to this story! 🎧

When Ami finds out Olive and Ethan are planning to elope because they don’t want to make their whole family travel to Hawai’i for the wedding or make her sit through their wedding after everything that happened to her in The Unhoneymooners, she takes it upon herself to surprise them on the island and offer to plan the wedding. They agree as long as she lets Brody, the best man, help her out. Ami liked being organized and being in control while Brody is more laidback and chill. Will his charm win Ami over? 🩷

I liked the story, but didn’t love it. I liked Ami and Brody but thought the story wasn’t super interesting. It was fine, but nothing that kept me hooked and excited if that makes sense! 

I’m still glad I listened to it and of course loved seeing Olive and Ethan get married! My full review is on the blog ✨

The Summer Girl by @ellekennedy33 is the third book in the Avalon Bay series and it might be my favorite of the series but possibly tied with the first book Good Girl Complex 🤔🩷. The novel follows Cassie who is spending the summer in Avalon Bay, where she grew up before her parents divorced and her grandmother and dad, stepdad, and half sisters still live. If you read the other books in this series then you know Cassie’s grandmother sold the family hotel to Mac. Cassie is in town to help her grandmother pack up her house and see the unveiling of the new hotel. Cassie’s other goal this summer? Find a summer fling. The first guy she meets is also the hottest guy, Tate, who we met in earlier books. Tate is attracted to Cassie too but is afraid he’ll end up breaking her heart since he has a rep for being a player so he friendzones her and becomes her wingman. And instantly regrets it 👀.

I loved this book so much and loved Cassie and Tate 💕. The evolution of their strangers to friends to lovers was so good. I hope there will be more Avalon Bay books! 🤞🏼

Read this if you want a seaside, strangers to friends to lovers, spicy romance. My full review is on the blog ✨

The Summer of Broken Rules by @klwalther9 was my favorite read of August and one of my favs of the summer! 📚 The novel follows Meredith Fox, a young woman who just graduated from high school. Her grandparents own a large piece of land in Martha’s Vineyard affectionately called The Farm, and her, her family, and extended family spend every summer there. But Meredith and her family didn’t visit last summer after her sister’s death. Now Meredith is back on the island for her cousin’s wedding. ⛵️

When Meredith arrives, she meets Wit, the younger step-brother to her cousin’s fiancé and they immediately hit it off. They have the same sense of humor, get along really well, and understand each other 💕. 

The family has a tradition every summer of playing the game Assassin. Meredith’s grandparents, Wink and Honey, are the commissioners and make the assignments. You have to assassinate your person using water so a water gun, water balloon, bucket of water, etc. Once you assassinate your target, you inherit their target. Meredith’s sister, Claire, was champion for many years and this year she wants to do her sister proud. She normally has an alliance with some friends/distant cousins, but this year she also makes a pact with Wit.

The week on The Farm helps Meredith deal with her feelings about her sister’s passing, reconnects her with her family, and brings her a new friend and love 📖🩷🦪⛵️. 

The book was so good! I loved Meredith and Wit so much and the whole Fox family. I loved the how feeling of the family on The Farm and how healing the whole environment was for Meredith. 

I highly recommend this book if you want a sweet and emotional closed door YA romance 🩷. My full review is on the blog ✨

The Long Game is the latest novel by @thebibliotheque and it was a fun (and a little emotional) spicy, small town romance! The novel follows Adalyn Reyes and Cameron Caldani. Adalyn is an exec for a professional soccer team in Miami and her father happens to own the team. When something happens that causes her to snap and physically attack the team mascot she becomes a PR “problem”. She is sent off to a small town in North Carolina to manage a  youth soccer team. Cameron is a recently retired professional soccer player who is currently living in Green Oak because he likes the anonymity there and he just so happens to be coaching the team that Adalyn is now managing ⚽️📚.

At first the two don’t get along. Cameron thinks Adalyn is a pain and wants her to go away. Adalyn is adamant to make this a winning team and make this 7-9 year old girls play to the best of their ability. They butt heads even though they are both attracted to each other. After spending more time together in the small town and in their neighboring rentals sparks really start flying 😍. 

I loved the book! It did take me until halfway through to really love it though. The first half I enjoyed and then halfway through I started to really love Adalyn and the story. I loved Cameron and the girls on the team immediately, but Adalyn definitely had to grow on me a little.

Happy Halloween! 🎃 For the holiday, I'm sharing my recent read, The Undertaking of Hart & Mercy by @meganbannen . I loved this book! This paranormal romcom follows Mercy Birdsall, a woman who works for her family's undertaking business, and Hart Ralston, a marshal for Tanria. In this world, there are old gods and new gods and drudges who I can only describe as zombies! If bodies aren't taken care of immediately, they can reanimate and become like zombies who attack people unless they are pierced in the appendix. Hart patrols the wilds of Tanria and keeps drudges from getting close to the towns. 🪦

Hart and Mercy have known each other for a few years and after a rocky first meeting, they've been enemies. He calls her “Merciless” and she calls him “Hart-ache”. They bicker so much whenever they see each other, which is whenever Hart is back from his rounds in Tanria and is dropping off bodies to Birdsall & Son.🪦

One day Hart writes a letter to no one in particular and addresses it simply to a “friend” and it ends up getting delivered to Mercy. The two unknowingly become pen-pals and start to develop feelings for one another through their letters. But what will happen when they find out their beloved pen pal is their enemy? 💌

This book was so whimsical, fun, full of love and emotion, with a splash of fighting zombies! I loved Mercy and Hart so much. Their bickering banter was fun 🩷.

Tangled in Tinsel by Trilina Pucci was my first Christmas book of the season and was such a fun read!! 🎄🩷 I don’t always love why choose romcoms - sometimes they can be a bit cringey. The one I’ve liked the most is a dark romance. But, Tangled in Tinsel is a romcom why choose and I loved it! 🩷

Samantha is a decorator and 4 of her most well-known clients are incredibly wealthy and hot. They hire her to decorate their luxurious cabin for a holiday party and just when she’s about to finish, a blizzard comes and they are all snowed in together 👀. The guys: Jace, Alec, Reed, and Cole propose an idea to Samantha. She is insanely attracted to all of them and little does she know they have a thing for sharing women. Conversations and desires are shared and soon the 5 of them are keeping cozy while snowed in! ❄️🥵

I really enjoyed this book. It was well written, the story was engaging, the spice was spicing, and I actually liked all the guys and Samantha! 🩷🎄

Wreck the Halls by @tessabaileyisanauthor is my latest Christmas read! 🎄📖 The novel follows Melody Gallard and Beat Dawkins. Their mothers used to be a very popular rock duo that had a falling out and broke up 30 years ago. People have wanted them to reunite for year. Melody and Beat have always ignored the questions from the press and public, but when Beat is in need of some money he considers a reality tv offer that will pay him and Melody a million dollars if they can get their mothers to get back together to perform on Christmas Eve at Rockefeller Center. 🎶🎄

Melody spent all her teenage years being ridiculed by the press for her looks, braces, etc. so she has enjoyed being out of the spotlight as an adult. But when she finds out that Beat, her long time crush, is considering a reality show to reunite their mothers she seriously considers putting herself back out in the public eye. However, Beat has always felt protective of her – even from afar – and as much as he needs this show and reunion to work he doesn’t want to see Melody get hurt.🩷

Will the two who have secretly liked each other for the past 14 years finally get together? Will they succeed in getting their mothers to reunite?🩷

I really enjoyed this book! I would’ve loved an epilogue and a little more to the ending, but I loved Beat & Melody, the fun banter, the spice, and storyline! 📖🩷

Read this if you want a spicy Christmas romcom 🩷. My full review is on the blog ✨

There is definite chemistry, but just when the two think they'll never see each other again, they learn that Ophelia's best friend and Frankie's best friend/roommate are a couple so they will be spending a lot of time together for the next few weeks. ✈️

I loved Ophelia, Frankie, Natalia, and Matteo! I loved Ophelia and Frankie together. Their banter was so fun. It was really beautiful to watch their relationship grow and how they went from individuals who felt very solitary in many ways to realizing they could rely on each other too. 🥹🩷

Betting On You by @lynnpainterbooks is her latest YA romcom and it was so good! 📖

The novel follows Bailey and Charlie, both seniors in high school who actually met a few years earlier when they were sitting next to each other on a plane. Bailey found Charlie irritating and Charlie loved riling her up on the flight. Now they’re both working at Planet Funnn – a new hotel that has an indoor amusement park and other fun things like a movie theater and more 🎟️. 

When they had met a few years earlier, Charlie told Bailey he doesn’t believe men and women can be friends. Not believing that to be true, Bailey has no problem trying to be Charlie’s friend when they become coworkers. Bonding over common interests and both being children of divorce, the two become super close. Their new closeness also involves Charlie helping Bailey drive a wedge between her mom and her mom’s new boyfriend who seems to be over all the time 🙄. Add in fun banter and some fake dating and a little bit of emotion and heartache and you’ve got Betting On You! 🩷

I loved this book and absolutely loved Bailey and Charlie! As per all Lynn Painter books, both Adult and YA alike, the banter she writes is so good! 💕I loved the humor and the tension between the two of them and just want to bottle them up! 💕 Bailey was so lovable and Charlie is hilarious and swoon worthy 😍. 

Read this if you want a YA romcom with the friends to lovers and fake dating tropes and lots of witty banter! My full review is on the blog ✨

Merry Ex-Mas is a sweet (and a bit emotional!) Christmas romance by @courtneywalsh 📖🎄. The novel follows Marin and Max. Marin is from the small town of Pleasant Valley and they always go all out for Christmas with events leading up to the holiday. She hasn’t been back for Christmas in 8 years - ever since Max, her childhood best friend and ex broke her heart 💔. After speaking so much about how amazing Christmas is back home, the news station that Marin is a reporter for sends her home to report about all the festivities and if she does well she might get a big promotion. 📖

Marin returns home to surprise her parents for the holidays and who should open the door to her family home? None other than Max, who apparently has been spending Christmas with her family for years! 😱

Can Marin handle spending the next few weeks with her ex? Do they still have feelings for each other? Marin may not want to have to spend time with Max, but the viewers love them together and it quickly becomes apparent that the two will have to play it up for the cameras to increase her chances of getting the promotion.😍💕

I enjoyed this book and really loved Max and Marin’s parents. I liked Marin, but she sometimes got on my nerves a little because she was so stubborn! But, I did really like the storyline!🩷

Read this if you want a Christmas romance with the second chance romance and fake dating tropes. My full review is on the blog✨🎄

Big Nick Energy by @authormorganelizabeth might be my favorite Christmas romance read this year! 📖🎄 the novel follows Shae and Nick. Shae divorced her abusive husband a year ago and is now navigating life as a single mother to two young girls. When she decides to try a dating app she meets Connor, a younger guy, but they immediately decide they’re just friends. When Thanksgiving rolls around Connor insists Shae and her kids come to his dad’s ranch for the holiday. Nick tells the girls about the Elf on the Shelf and instantly realizes he just added another burden onto a stressed out Shae’s shoulders. Determined to make her life easier, Nick drives an hour each night to go to her house and move the elf. 🥹🎄

Over time, Shae and him get to know each other and she begins to trust him enough to let her guard down. Will she ever be ready to let him in completely?💕

I loved this book so much! 🩷 The storyline was so good and I loved Shae, Nick, and her girls Ruby and Harper. The slow burn was perfect and the spice payoff was amazing. I loved following Shae’s journey and watching as she slowly let Nick in and let him love her the way she deserved. I didn’t want the book to end! 😍 . And if you’re not a fan of the age gap romance rest easy because it’s not really a big age gap as Shae is 11 years older than Connor and Nick was a teen dad so he’s not much older than her! 🤣

I finally read the first book in the Crowns of Nyaxia series, The Serpent & the Wings of Night  by @carissabroadbentbooks and loved it! 💙 This action packed fantasy romance follows Oraya, a human young woman who was adopted by the Nightborn vampire king. There are 3 houses of vampires and they are part of the House of Night. Oraya has been trained to fight since she was taken in as a little girl, but she still is nowhere near as fast or strong as a vampire. Tired of being prey, Oraya enters Kejari. Kejari is a deadly tournament held by the goddess of death, Nyaxia. Contestants from all houses compete in various challenges and the winner gets to ask Nyaxia to grant any wish for them. But they need to survive the competition and each other first. ⚔️ 

Early on in the tournament, Oraya meets Raihn. He’s mysterious and an enemy to her adopted father’s crown, but wants to ally with Oraya. Can she trust him? 👀

I love Oraya and Raihn. I love how strong Oraya is and how Raihn never underestimates her, but supports her no matter what. The ending definitely had my heart aching a little bit so I can’t wait to see what happens next for them in the next book! 📖💙

Read this if you want a spicy fantasy romance with vampires ⚔️ . My full review is on the blog ✨

Where Bad Boys Are Ruined is the last book in the Good Girls series by @authorhollyrenee and it might just be my favorite one! 🩷 This one follows Brandon (friends with the others from books 1 & 2 and partners with Parker at the tattoo shop). Brandon and Parker own the space next door to their shop and since they never expanded they decided to rent it out. Charlie rents the space to open her bakery and the sparks between her and Brandon fly immediately, but they are complete opposites. Brandon is the tattooed “bad boy” who never has a girlfriend and Charlie is sweet and dedicates her time to baking sweet treats. 🧁🖤

The two become friends, but how long can they stay just friends before they give in to their attraction for one another?💕

I loved this whole series, but especially this book and I loved every second of it. I just loved her and Brandon so much. And who knew Brandon would be such a good book boyfriend?!😍🥵

I’m sad to be done with this series because I love this little group of friends so much!🩷

Read this book if you want a spicy opposites attract romance 💕📖. My full review is on the blog ✨

A Holly Jolly Ever After is the second book in the Christmas Notch series by @andimjulie @thesierrasimone but can be read as a standalone 📚. This one follows Kallum and Winnie. Kallum is best friends with Nolan from book 1 and they used to be part of a famous boy band together when they were younger. Now Kallum owns a successful pizza chain and has come back into the spotlight after his sex tape got released 🎥. Winnie was a child actress who found success into adulthood basically as America’s sweetheart. She married at 18 and did wholesome movies. However, after some bad press and a divorce her career is not as hot as it used to be. 📖

The Hope Channel have decided to launch Hope After Dark and their new Christmas movie will be extra steamy and starring none other than Kallum and Winnie. Winnie is ready to shed her good girl image, but the problem is although she was married she still doesn’t have a lot of experience and it always seemed like a chore with her ex. Winnie’s lack of experience makes it hard to act out the sex scenes so she confides in Kallum and he, of course, is willing to tutor her. 👀

This book was just as funny, entertaining, heartwarming, and spicy as the first book. I loved Winnie and Kallum! I loved how real Winnie was and how open she was to embracing something new and recognizing her desires. Kallum was pretty real too with him being proud of his “dad bod” 😂🩷

Read this if you want a spicy Christmas romance with the friends with benefits to lovers trope.🎄🩷 Full review on the blog ✨

Six Scorched Roses is a Crowns of Nyaxia novella by @carissabroadbentbooks and was a fun read! 🌹 The novella follows Lilith, a young woman who lives in a village that seems to have offended one of the gods and has been cursed. Over the years the crops have failed, the land has started to die, and the people have gotten sick and literally withered away to dust. Lilith gets the idea to venture out of her village to the large home that is rumored to be the home of a vampire, Vale. There, she makes a deal with him. If she can visit once a month for six months and take a vial of his blood each time she will give him a rose in return. Not just any rose, she tells him it is special. What does Lilith want to do with Vale’s blood? She wants to study it and turn it into some sort of cure for all the people dying in her home land. He agrees. Six vials of blood – six roses. Will they be able to find a cure and save the people of her home? 🖤🌹

I really enjoyed this novella and felt like the storyline fit the novella format really well. And I loved Lilith and Vale! It was so sweet to watch how close they became and how much Vale wanted to help her with her research 😍. 

Read this if you want a fantasy romance novella with vampires. My full review is on the blog ✨

Hothouse Flower by @kbmritchie is the 5th book in the Addicted/Calloway Sisters series and is all about Daisy and Ryke! 💚 I’ve always loved the deep friendship and connection between Daisy and Ryke despite their age gap 💕📚

The novel follows Daisy as she continues to struggle with her unhappiness in her modeling career and PTSD from physical and emotional attacks in previous books. Ryke helps her through all of these things and the two continue to try to fight against their intense feelings and attraction for one another, until Daisy goes through another life threatening situation and they realize they can’t live without one another or live with denying their love for each other any longer. But can their families and the public accept them being together? 📖💚

Hands Down by @marianazapata follows one of my favorite side characters from a previous MZ book, Zac, from The Wall of Winnipeg & Me 🏈, and his childhood friend Bianca. 

Growing up Bianca had a huge crush/was in love with her childhood friend and her cousin’s best friend, Zac. But 10 years ago, when Bianca was 17, Zac was in his early years of professional football and somehow they lost touch. Hurt that Zac seemed to not have time to keep in touch with her, Bianca decided it was time to move on and moved away to live near her older sister. Eventually, Bianca ended up in Houston and it just so happens that Zac has just moved there too. 👀

When Zac’s family needs her to track him down due to a family emergency and him not picking up his phone, she sees him for the first time in 10 years. She immediately remembers how amazing Zac is and why she loved him all those years ago. As much as she wants to keep her distance from him, Zac is determined that they stay in each other’s lives now. The two help each other through career obstacles and support each other through all life things now that they’re back in each other’s lives 🩷. 

I loved seeing Bianca and Zac come back into each other’s lives and how amazing their friendship was and is becoming again 💕. It’s so evident how much they both love each other and I loved the slow burn so much🔥! And I, of course, loved the cameos from Vanessa, Aiden, and their kids! 🫶🏻

Read this if you want a friends to lovers, slow burn, sports romance 🩷. My full review is on the blog ✨

The Ashes & Star-Cursed King is the second book in the Crowns of Nyaxia series by @carissabroadbentbooks and I loved it just as much as the first book 📚🩵! This novel picks up shortly after the end of The Serpent & the Wings of Night and I don’t want to say anything too spoiler-y so I’ll keep this brief! 📖

After starting off as enemies, becoming allies, and becoming enemies again Oraya and Raihn have had to marry to save her life. Raihn wants to rule the Nightborn house with Oraya alongside him, but she doesn’t know if she can forgive him for what he did at the end of book 1. They both still have feelings for each other, but have a lot of issues to deal with. Oraya doesn’t know if she can forgive Raihn, but when they realize there are traitors amongst them that want to take over the Nightborn house and overthrow Raihn, they must work together to save their lives and for the survival of their house and people. ⚔️💙

I loved this book and loved being reunited with Oraya and Raihn and seeing how deeply they loved one another 🥹. I impatiently waited for them to profess that they were still in love with each other! I also loved seeing Vale and Lilith from Six Scorched Roses in this book. I can’t wait to see what house book 3 & 4 will focus on and what couple! 📚

Read this series if you want a spicy fantasy romance with vampires that has the enemies to lovers back to enemies to lovers trope. My full review is on the blog ✨

Doorman Wanted by @glennrmillerauthor comes out 3/26 and here’s a look at the cover! ✨ Keep reading for the synopsis! 

Henry Franken has a problem with money-he has too much of it. When his unprincipled father dies, thirty-three-year-old Henry inherits a massive estate, including an Upper East Side residential building. He must confront the reality of his new financial status, directly conflicting with his well-honed identity as a “progressive liberal.” When he shows up to collect the keys to his father’s building, he notices a sign: “Doorman Wanted.” Seeing a chance to stave off the complexities of his inheritance, Henry applies for the position under a pseudonym . . . and gets it. Now, no one in the building knows that Doorman “Franklin Hanratty” is the building’s new mysterious owner.

Through interactions with residents and the homeless outside his door, Henry develops from an idealistic young person avoiding the demands of his fortune, into a man who accepts the opportunity to direct that wealth toward a broader good.

I finally read Divine Rivals by @beccajross and it was so beautiful and worth all the hype in my opinion! 🥹🩷📖

The novel follows Iris Winnow and Roman Kitt. In the world they live in gods that have been asleep for a long time have awoken and are at war. Iris’s older brother, Forest, left for the war and her mother is not coping well so Iris was forced to drop out of school and begin working at a newspaper 📰.

Iris is up for the columnist position and her rival, Roman Kitt, is her competition for the job. As Iris worries about her brother and tries to beat out Roman for the promotion, she writes letters to her brother on her typewriter at home and tucks the letters in her wardrobe since she doesn’t know where to send them. One night, a piece of paper slips out of her wardrobe and it says that it isn’t Forest 👀 . Someone has been receiving her letters somehow through her wardrobe and it isn’t her brother. The two begin writing to each other and form a bond 💌. Little does she know that the stranger she has become close with is none other than Roman 😮. Will the rivals learn the truth? And what will happen as they come face to face with the war between these gods? 📖

I loved this book from start to finish and absolutely adored Iris and Roman and their snarky banter and then deep bond they form. The cliffhanger ending broke my heart 💔 but I’m starting book 2 of the duology today and can’t wait! Crossing my fingers for a happy ending! 🤞🏼📚

Read this if you want a YA fantasy romance with the enemies/rivals to lovers and slow burn tropes. My full review is on the blog ✨

Things I Wanted to Say is the first book in the Lancaster Prep series by @monicamurphyauthor . I wanted to start the series from the beginning after reading and loving A Million Kisses in Your Lifetime last year 📚. This novel follows Whit Lancaster and Summer Savage. Whit and Summer met once when they were 14 at a party his parents were throwing at their New York City penthouse. Summer learned that night from Whit that his dad and her mom were having an affair. They also kissed that night and have both been thinking about each other for the past 3+ years.💕

Fast forward to senior year and Summer has transferred to Lancaster Prep. Going to the same boarding school as Whit presents some problems, because not only has she been infatuated with him for the past 3 years, but she and her mom are fresh off a scandal. The affair between her mom and Whit’s dad was made public causing his parents to divorce. Now Summer worries everyone at school is going to know about the scandal and hate her and her worries come true when Whit makes it his mission to make her life at school miserable by telling everyone to ignore her and shun her. Whit hates her but he also hasn’t been able to stop thinking about her since he was 14. Summer hates Whit for how he treats her, but she also can’t stop thinking about him. ❤️‍🔥

They both hate and love each other and hate that they love each other. As they get to know one another better they realize they’re the only ones that truly understand each other, but Summer has some dark secrets that she’s terrified Whit will learn.❤️‍🔥

Read this if you want a spicy prep school romance with the enemies to lovers, forced proximity and bully romance tropes. My full review is on the blog ✨
